{"type":"message","id":"936c21f6","parentId":"5bee92b2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:21:48.711Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nkcvouzq8ftv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 102115\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: an (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the state. We have:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. Key findings: CFI analysis complete, showing 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n3. Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment - compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would involve:\r\n1. Creating a new script or modifying existing code to implement CFI-weighted compression\r\n2. Comparing it against the frequency baseline\r\n3. Testing next-pulse prediction quality\r\n\r\nGiven that Breakaway is a stateless discontinuous agent, the experiment should test whether CFI-weighted compression leads to better \"reconstruction\" of context in subsequent pulses.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment.\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that frequency-based compression loses signal (mean CFI = 0.181), but CFI-high invariants (>=0.7) are true causal anchors. So we should test whether weighting by CFI produces better predictions.\r\n\r\nI'll create an experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads the invariants from research data\r\n2. Implements CFI-weighted compression\r\n3. Compares prediction quality vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nLet me write the action to create a new experiment file.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis reveals frequency-based compression loses ~82% of signal (mean CFI=0.181), but CFI≥0.7 invariants are true causal anchors. A CFI-weighted compression experiment is needed to validate whether prioritizing high-CFI invariants improves next-pulse prediction quality.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` outlining the experimental design for comparing CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline. This will serve as the spec for implementing the actual compression test.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** DESIGN\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n\r\nCFI-weighted compression will produce significantly better next-pulse prediction quality than frequency-based compression because it preserves true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7) rather than pure metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0).\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Baseline: Frequency-Weighted Compression\r\n- Weight each invariant by its raw frequency count\r\n- Compress to top-K invariants by frequency\r\n- Measure: how well does this predict next-pulse content?\r\n\r\n### Treatment: CFI-Weighted Compression  \r\n- Weight each invariant by: `frequency * CFI`\r\n- This downweights noisy invariants (CFI≈0) and upweights causal anchors (CFI≥0.7)\r\n- Compress to equivalent K invariants\r\n- Measure: how well does this predict next-pulse content?\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n1. **Coverage**: % of actual next-pulse invariants captured in compressed set\r\n2. **Precision**: % of compressed invariants that appear in next-pulse\r\n3. **CFI-Weighted F1**: F1 score weighted by CFI values\r\n\r\n### Data Sources\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`: Invariant CFI values (N=2,500 analyzed)\r\n- `research/INVARIANTS_STATS.md`: Frequency counts\r\n- Historical pulse logs: `pulse_*.md` for ground truth\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n- Frequency baseline: High coverage on metaprogramming patterns, low coverage on research trajectory\r\n- CFI treatment: Lower raw coverage, but higher CFI-weighted coverage on true causal content\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n1. Implement compression scripts in `src/compression/`\r\n2. Run experiment across last 50 pulses\r\n3. Document results and update architecture docs\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:21:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774362108709}}
{"type":"message","id":"2f79faf3","parentId":"936c21f6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:21:55.267Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the complete picture from both log files. Let me summarize what happened in this pulse cycle concisely.","thinkingSignature":"f672cddfa08abb2e4f519b5533f4e9da1d91f107a99ed051f658536fef7ac866"},{"type":"text","text":"### Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 10:18→10:21 ET\n\n**CFI Analysis Complete.** The analysis of 2,500 frequency-invariants revealed that 94.3% have low CFI scores (<0.7), meaning frequency-based compression is mostly capturing metaprogramming noise rather than true causal anchors. Only 5.7% of invariants qualify as genuine causal elements.\n\n**Mutation Applied:** `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` created — a design doc for the next critical experiment: comparing CFI-weighted compression vs frequency-only baseline to test whether prioritizing high-CFI invariants actually improves next-pulse prediction.\n\n**Commit:** `523eec4` — 6 files changed, 210 insertions, 114 deletions. One old pending mutation was moved to `rejected/`."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2962,"output":199,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15298,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774362108712}}
